p: The MICs ranged within 3.9–125.0 µL/mL (dilutions 1/8 to 1/256). The antifungal activity indicated that seed oil inhibited the growth of all tested fungi at all dilutions, except for ( 5), which was resistant against all concentrations ( Table 4). Orange essential oil has shown potential to control A. dauci and A. alternata [ 27]. Our results show that the bioactivity of the seed oil depended on the fungi isolates. The MIC values were 3.9 µL/mL for six fungal isolates and 15.6, 62.5 and 125.0 µL/mL for ( 6) , ( 4) and ( 3), respectively.
